  "task": "Implement asynchronous Byzantine-resilient linearizable consensus with multi-shard distributed transactions, formal liveness proof, and authenticated snapshot DAG. Build on v7 by adding: (1) Asynchronous Byzantine model — system operates in async model (no timing assumptions); tolerate up to ⌊(n-1)/3⌋ Byzantine nodes; prove safety without synchrony bounds; (2) Multi-shard linearizability — transactions can span multiple shards; all cross-shard reads/writes must appear in single total order; linearization points must respect causal dependencies across shards; (3) Formal liveness proof — prove system makes progress under transient partitions; every non-faulty node eventually gets response within bounded rounds; (4) Authenticated snapshot DAG — snapshots form a DAG (not linear chain); each snapshot authenticated by ≥2f+1 nodes; causal edges represent 'happens-before' relationships; (5) View-change safety — prove safety maintained across all view changes; no two different blocks committed in same height across views; (6) Quorum read freshness — read operations must prove they read from ≥f+1 replicas of leader's view without stale data; bound staleness to <100ms",
